claim.claim-text:
A charging system of a biped walking robot (10) for charging a battery (11) provided in a biped walking robot (10), comprising:
seating and retaining means (2) on which the biped walking robot (10) can sit and which retains the biped walking robot (10) at a seated posture;
a power feeding connector (3) to be connected to a power receiving connector (12) provided in the biped walking robot (10) when the biped walking robot (10) sits on the seating and retaining means (2);
connection detecting means (50) for detecting whether the power receiving connector (12) and the power feeding connector (3) are in a connected state;
a charging power source (60) for supplying charging current to the battery (11); and
charging control means (4) for charging the battery (11) by supplying charging current to the battery (11) from the charging power source (60) through the power feeding connector (3) and the power receiving connector (12) when the connection detecting means (50) detects that the power receiving connector (12) and the power feeding connector (3) are in the connected state,
wherein the power feeding connector (3) comprises a first charging terminal (30a, 30j) for outputting charging current and the power receiving connector (12) comprises a second charging terminal (22a, 22j) that is brought into conduction with the first charging terminal (30a, 30j), characterized in that
the power feeding connector (3) comprises a first detecting terminal (30b to 30i) for detecting whether the power receiving connector (12) and the power feeding connector (3) are in the connected state and the power receiving connector (12) comprises a second detecting terminal (22b to 22i) that is brought into conduction with the first detecting terminal (30b to 30i) when the power receiving connector (12) is connected with the power feeding connector (3),
the connection detecting means (50) detects that the power feeding connector (3) and the power receiving connector (12) are in the connected state when the first detecting terminal (30b to 30i) and the second detecting terminal (22b to 22i) are brought into conduction and
the supply of charging current by the charging power source (60) is started after the connection detecting means (50) detects said connected state.
